What is Indexing in MongoDB?

Indexing is a technique used to improve query performance.

ğŸ‘‰ Indexes help MongoDB find data faster without scanning the entire collection.

ğŸ“Œ Without index â†’ Full Collection Scan
ğŸ“Œ With index â†’ Fast Search using index

ğŸ”· Why Indexing is Needed?

Faster find() queries

Improves sorting performance

Efficient filtering on large data

Essential for production applications

ğŸ”· How Index Works (Easy Example)

Without Index:

MongoDB checks every document


With Index:

MongoDB directly jumps to matching data

ğŸ”· Create Index
Create Single Field Index
db.students.createIndex({ name: 1 })


1 â†’ Ascending

-1 â†’ Descending

Create Multiple Field (Compound) Index
db.students.createIndex({ course: 1, age: -1 })


ğŸ“Œ Order of fields matters.

ğŸ”· Types of Indexes (Very Important)
1ï¸âƒ£ Single Field Index
db.students.createIndex({ email: 1 })

2ï¸âƒ£ Compound Index
db.students.createIndex({ course: 1, year: 1 })

3ï¸âƒ£ Unique Index

Prevents duplicate values.

db.users.createIndex({ email: 1 }, { unique: true })

4ï¸âƒ£ Text Index

Used for text search.

db.articles.createIndex({ title: "text", description: "text" })


Search:

db.articles.find({ $text: { $search: "mongodb" } })

5ï¸âƒ£ Hashed Index

Used for sharding.

db.users.createIndex({ userId: "hashed" })

6ï¸âƒ£ TTL (Time To Live) Index

Automatically deletes documents after time.

db.sessions.createIndex(
  { createdAt: 1 },
  { expireAfterSeconds: 3600 }
)

ğŸ”· View Indexes
db.students.getIndexes()

ğŸ”· Drop Index
db.students.dropIndex({ name: 1 })

ğŸ”· Explain() â€“ Check Index Usage
db.students.find({ name: "Amit" }).explain("executionStats")


ğŸ“Œ Shows whether index is used or not.

ğŸ”· Indexing Rules (Important for Viva)

Index improves read, slows write

Too many indexes reduce performance

Use index on frequently queried fields

MongoDB automatically creates index on _id

ğŸ”· Indexing in MERN (Mongoose Example)
const userSchema = new mongoose.Schema({
  email: { type: String, unique: true },
  name: String
})

userSchema.index({ name: 1 })
